<subSubSection id="46866550E53EB30A2BBDF8C2FC4E38C3" pageId="1" pageNumber="274" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0E2336DBE53EB30A2BBDF8C2FF09386F" blockId="1.[136,1452,1664,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis id="3CE8EAC9E53EB30A2BBDF8C2FEB43853" bold="true" box="[189,328,1844,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="274">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The epithet refers to the locality (Doi Suthep) where the 
<typeStatus id="D1278879E53EB30A2F08F8C3FBC43852" box="[1032,1080,1845,1871]" pageId="1" pageNumber="274">type</typeStatus>
specimens of this species were collected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E2336DBE53EB30A2BBDF88AFC4E38C3" blockId="1.[136,1452,1664,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis id="3CE8EAC9E53EB30A2BBDF88AFEF5388B" bold="true" box="[189,265,1916,1942]" pageId="1" pageNumber="274">Notes:</emphasis>
—This species is widely distributed in northern, central, eastern, southeastern, southwestern, and southern 
<collectingCountry id="768B764BE53EB30A2B88F856FF1338A7" box="[136,239,1952,1978]" name="Thailand" pageId="1" pageNumber="274">Thailand</collectingCountry>
; its morphology is somewhat heterogeneous (pers. obs., CW &amp; TC) and, therefore, this name might consist of more than one species, awaiting molecular phylogenetic clarification.
</paragraph>
